      "line": 111,
      "message": "The prepare methods do too much and hide some of its functionalities. Besides preparing the delegateExecution object they also create the instance of the tested class under the hood. Suggested fix - just create the PnfCheckInputs instance inside the test methods explicitly. The private methods do not improve that much -> you still end up with the same ammount of code specific to each variable and in addition have to jump inside the 'prepare' methods to see what it is being set. Some of this can just be be inlined.",
